and Province]]||The first [[Pajhwok Afghan News]] and [[BBC News]] journalist to be killed after being abducted and found dead the next day. His captors taunted him with the fate of Ajmal Naqshbandi before killing him.||<ref>{{cite news|title=BBC Afghan reporter is shot dead |url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/south_asia/7442772.stm |publisher=BBC News |date=2008-06-08 |accessdate=2012-12-26}}</ref> |- |{{dts|15 January 2008}}||[[Carsten Thomassen (journalist)|Carsten Thomassen]] {{Flagicon|Norway}}||Kabul||The Norwegian journalist worked for ''[[Dagbladet]]'' and was killed in a Taliban terrorist [[2008 Kabul Serena Hotel attack|attack on a hotel]] in the capital.||<ref>{{cite news|title=Taleban attack Kabul luxury hotel |url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/7187592.stm |publisher=BBC News |date=2008-01-15 |accessdate=2012-12-26}}</ref> |- |{{dts|6 June 2007}}||[[Zakia Zaki]]||[[Jabal Saraj]], [[Parwan Province]]||Shot in her home, she was the owner of a radio station and a critic of the Taliban.||<ref>{{cite news|title=Husband reveals threats to Afghan journalist |url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/south_asia/6745529.stm |publisher=BBC News |date=2007-06-14 |accessdate=2012-12-26}}</ref> |- |{{dts|8 April 2007}}||[[Ajmal Naqshbandi]]||Helmand Province||He was the fixer for kidnapped [[Italy|Italian]]-[[Switzerland|Swiss]] journalist [[Daniele Mastrogiacomo]] of [[La Repubblica]]. His execution was the subject of a documentary film. The team driver Sayed Agha was also killed.||<ref>{{cite news |title=Execution video raises concerns for Afghan hostages |url=http://www.euronews.com/2007/04/11/execution-video-raises-concerns-for-afghan-hostages/ |publisher=Euronews |date=2007-11-04 |accessdate=2012-12-26}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/south_asia/6537097.stm |title=Taleban kill Afghanistan reporter |publisher=BBC News |date=2007-04-08 |accessdate=2012-12-26}}</ref> |- |{{dts|7 October 2006}}||[[Death of Karen Fischer and Christian Struwe|Christian Struwe]] {{