'''Ralph Burkei''' (15 December 1956, [[Munich]] – 26 November 2008) was a German [[TV producer]] and co-owner of the [[Bavaria]]n [[production company]] C.A.M.P. TV. He was also active in Bavarian local politics with the Munich [[Christian Social Union of Bavaria|CSU]] party and was its treasurer from 2000 to 2004. At one time, he was vice-president of the [[TSV 1860 München]] and president of the [[Lokomotive Leipzig|VfB Leipzig]] football teams.<ref>[http://www.br-online.de/aktuell/news/burkei-tod-bombay-ID1227782863172.xml Anschläge in Bombay, Münchner Unternehmer Burkei tot ''in German''] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20081210125213/http://www.br-online.de/aktuell/news/burkei-tod-bombay-ID1227782863172.xml |date=10 December 2008 }}</ref> Burkei died on the way to hospital after fleeing armed attackers and falling from the facade of the [[Taj Mahal Palace & Tower|Taj Mahal hotel]] during the [[2008 Mumbai attacks]].<ref>[http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/hr/content_display/world/news/e3iacfb4ddfa5a1002b40aea0ca93b171e5 German TV producer dies in Mumbai]</ref>

