'''Roger de Saint-Lary de Bellegarde''' (died 1579) was a member of an important [[France|French]] family.
He served with distinction in the wars against the French [[Huguenot|Protestants]]. He showed much devotion to [[Henry III of France|Henry III]], who loaded him with favours and made him [[marshal]] of France. He eventually fell into disgrace, however, and died by poisoning in 1579.
