'''William Pairman Brown''' was a Scottish amateur [[association football|football]] [[inside forward]] who played in the [[Scottish Football League|Scottish League]] for [[Queen's Park F.C.|Queen's Park]].<ref name="QPFC">{{cite web | access-date=11 October 2016 | url=http://www.qpfc.com/appearances/b/brownwp.htm | title=QPFC.com – A Historical Queen's Park FC Website | website=www.qpfc.com}}</ref>
== Personal life == Brown fought in the [[Highland Light Infantry]] during the [[First World War]], rising to the rank of [[sergeant]].<ref name="McCrossan">{{cite web|url=http://www.queensparkfc.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Frank-McCrossan-And-The-Great-War-A4.pdf|title=Queen's Park And The Great War: 1914 To 1918|last=|first=|date=|website=|publisher=|page=4|accessdate=13 October 2016}}</ref>
